king\",\"thinking\":\"\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2625,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":45359,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2625},\"output_tokens\":8,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYwGj5mSqovm8Tn1PNzBG\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"6f28d9e1-e016-49ed-8f9d-c7e455a7ee4f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-11T12:12:59.529Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6f28d9e1-e016-49ed-8f9d-c7e455a7ee4f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d79106a5-a980-46f7-b56d-1c2701ed4a9d\",\"version\":\"2.1.72\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/add-support-for-different-remote-for-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"refactored-shimmying-meteor\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01NFB9TY2gq47TYZqo2bCEQp\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good question. Assuming \\\"origin\\\" is the remote name is fragile — people rename remotes, and fork setups vary.\\n\\nThe cleanest answer: **use the remote that git passes to `PrePush`**. The pre-push hook already receives the remote the user is actively pushing to. That gives us both things we need:\\n\\n1. **Protocol** — parse that remote's URL to derive SSH vs HTTPS for the checkpoint remote\\n2. **Owner for fork detection** — parse that remote's URL to get the owner, compare to the checkpoint_remote owner\\n\\nThis works naturally for fork scenarios:\\n\\n| Push target | Remote URL | Owner | Checkpoint setting | Match? | Result |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| `origin` (non-fork) | `git@github.com:org/repo.git` | `org` | `org/checkpoints` | yes | push checkpoints |\\n| `origin` (fork) | `git@github.com:alice/repo.git` | `alice` | `org/checkpoints` | no | skip |\\n| `upstream` (from fork) | `git@github.com:org/repo.git` | `org` | `org/checkpoints` | yes | push checkpoints |\\n\\nNo need to guess which remote is \\\"the real origin\\\" — git tells us directly in the hook.\\n\\nThe one gap: **outside of `PrePush`** (e.g., `entire enable --checkpoint-remote`), where there's no hook argument. There you'd need a fallback. Options:\\n\\n- Check `branch.<current>.remote` from git config (the tracking remote for the current branch)\\n- Fall back to `origin` if that's not set\\n- Or just don't do fork detection at setup time — only at push time, where we always have the remote\\n\\nI'd go with the last one. At `entire enable` time, just write the setting. Fork detection only matters when actually pushing, and that's where we have the remote for free.\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2625,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":45359,\"output_tokens\":1734,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2625,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYwGj5mSqovm8Tn1PNzBG\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"13ad6574-c44c-48b3-a0b1-59883366b801\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-11T12:13:08.442Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"13ad6574-c44c-48b3-a0b1-59883366b801\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d79106a5-a980-46f7-b56d-1c2701ed4a9d\",\"version\":\"2.1.72\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/add-support-for-different-remote-for-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"refactored-shimmying-meteor\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"d70a00c7-fa50-4f0c-9ca3-987ded6a76fb\",\"toolUseID\":\"d70a00c7-fa50-4f0c-9ca3-987ded6a76fb\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-1