\\\"encoding/json\\\"\\n\\nfunc Unmarshal(data []byte, v any) error\\n    Unmarshal parses the JSON-encoded data and stores the result in the\\n    value pointed to by v. If v is nil or not a pointer, Unmarshal returns an\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"uuid\":\"3748ce3f-aee4-402c-ab31-225c74c01cf1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-11T12:16:56.060Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a215861cdf29eb6be\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01DJ68p67KEWsEw8TpHkZ1HA\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_014xq2sFnrZdVH2AHmSrfmjV\",\"uuid\":\"b6acdcd5-a255-4a1f-b1f2-d5643c5e35ae\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-11T12:16:56.061Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b6acdcd5-a255-4a1f-b1f2-d5643c5e35ae\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d79106a5-a980-46f7-b56d-1c2701ed4a9d\",\"version\":\"2.1.72\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/add-support-for-different-remote-for-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"refactored-shimmying-meteor\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Agent\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_014xq2sFnrZdVH2AHmSrfmjV\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_014xq2sFnrZdVH2AHmSrfmjV\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-11T12:18:35.920Z\",\"uuid\":\"e3c808b1-5bef-4b41-8011-a9076d9b7cc6\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d368e9ef-5fe8-43cc-bbb7-4405ea0fdd02\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d79106a5-a980-46f7-b56d-1c2701ed4a9d\",\"version\":\"2.1.72\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/add-support-for-different-remote-for-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"refactored-shimmying-meteor\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_014xq2sFnrZdVH2AHmSrfmjV\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I have everything I need. When `strategy_options` is deserialized as `map[string]any`, a JSON object like `{\\\"provider\\\": \\\"github\\\", \\\"repo\\\": \\\"org/repo\\\"}` will become `map[string]any{\\\"provider\\\": \\\"github\\\", \\\"repo\\\": \\\"org/repo\\\"}` -- which is the standard Go JSON behavior. The existing code already handles this through `StrategyOptions map[string]any`.\\n\\nNow let me formulate the complete implementation plan.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Detailed Implementation Plan: Checkpoint Remote Redesign\\n\\n### Overview\\n\\nThe current implementation stores a raw URL string in `strategy_options.checkpoint_remote`. The redesign changes this to a structured `{\\\"provider\\\": \\\"github\\\", \\\"repo\\\": \\\"org/repo\\\"}` format and derives the actual git URL at push time by inspecting the push remote's protocol (SSH vs HTTPS). This also adds fork detection (owner comparison) and smarter remote management.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Step 1: Settings Layer (`settings/settings.go` + `settings/settings_checkpoint_remote_test.go`)\\n\\n**Goal**: Change `GetCheckpointRemote()` to return a structured type instead of a raw string. Support both the new structured format and the legacy string format for backward compatibility.\\n\\n**Changes to `settings/settings.go`**:\\n\\n1. Define a new type:\\n```go\\n// CheckpointRemoteConfig holds the structured checkpoint remote configuration.\\n// Stored in strategy_options.checkpoint_remote as {\\\"provider\\\": \\\"github\\\", \\\"repo\\\": \\\"org/repo\\\"}.\\ntype CheckpointRemoteConfig struct {\\n    Provider string // e.g., \\\"github\\\"\\n    Repo     string // e.g., \\\"org/checkpoints-repo\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n2. Replace `GetCheckpointRemote() string` with `GetCheckpointRemote() *CheckpointRemoteConfig`:\\n   - When `strategy_options[\\\"checkpoint_remote\\\"]` is a `map[string]any` (new format): extract `provider` and `repo` fields, return a `*CheckpointRemoteConfig`.\\n   - When it's a `string` (legacy format): return `nil` (or optionally try to parse it, but per the spec we're migrating away from raw URLs). Actually, for backward compatibility, we should probably parse legacy strings like `git@github.com:org/repo.git` into the structured format. But the simpler approach is to just warn and ignore legacy strings, since this is a brand-new feature that hasn't shipped widely.\\n   - When not set or invalid: return `nil`.\\n\\n3. Add a helper method `Owner()` on `CheckpointRemoteConfig` that extracts the owner from the repo field (split on `/`, take first part).\\n\\n**Changes to `settings/settings_checkpoint_remote_test.go`**:\\n\\nRewrite all tests to reflect the new structured format:\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_NotConfigured` -- returns nil\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_StructuredGithub` -- `{\\\"provider\\\": \\\"github\\\", \\\"repo\\\": \\\"org/checkpoints\\\"}` returns correct config\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_EmptyRepo` -- returns nil\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_LegacyStringIgnored` -- old string format returns nil (or logs warning)\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_WrongType` -- numeric value returns nil\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_JSONRoundTrip` -- load from file, verify structured parsing\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_CoexistsWithPushSessions` -- both settings work together\\n- `TestCheckpointRemoteConfig_Owner` -- verify owner extraction\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Step 2: URL Derivation and Git URL Parsing (new file or in `checkpoint_remote.go`)\\n\\n**Goal**: Add functions to parse a git remote URL and derive a checkpoint URL in the same protocol.\\n\\n**New functions in `checkpoint_remote.go`**:\\n\\n1. `parseGitRemoteURL(remoteURL string) (protocol string, host string, owner string, repo string, err error)`:\\n   - Handle SSH format: `git@github.com:org/repo.git` -> `(\\\"ssh\\\", \\\"github.com\\\", \\\"org\\\", \\\"repo\\\")`\\n   - Handle HTTPS format: `https://github.com/org/repo.git` -> `(\\\"https\\\", \\\"github.com\\\", \\\"org\\\", \\\"repo\\\")`\\n   - Handle SSH with protocol: `ssh://git@github.com/org/repo.git`\\n   - Strip `.git` suffix if present\\n\\n2. `deriveCheckpointURL(pushRemoteURL string, checkpointRepo string) (string, error)`:\\n   - Parse the push remote URL to determine protocol and host\\n   - Construct the checkpoint URL using the same protocol:\\n     - SSH: `git@github.com:org/checkpoints-repo.git`\\n     - HTTPS: `https://github.com/org/checkpoints-repo.git`\\n   - This ensures credentials/auth work automatically\\n\\n3. `extractOwnerFromRemoteURL(remoteURL string) string`:\\n   - Convenience wrapper that returns just the owner from a git remote URL\\n   - Used for fork detection\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Step 3: Fork Detection (`checkpoint_remote.go`)\\n\\n**Goal**: At PrePush time, compare the push remote's owner to the checkpoint remote's owner.\\n\\n**New function**:\\n\\n`checkForkMismatch(ctx context.Context, pushRemoteName string, checkpointConfig *settings.CheckpointRemoteConfig) bool`:\\n- Run `git remote get-url <pushRemoteName>` to get the push remote URL\\n- Extract owner from the push remote URL\\n- Extract owner from `checkpointConfig.Repo` (split on `/`)\\n- If owners differ, log a warning and return `true` (skip pushing)\\n- This handles the fork scenario: when someone forks a repo, their push remote points to their fork (`theirorg/repo`) but the checkpoint_remote still points to the original org. Pushing checkpoints to the original org's repo would fail or be unwanted.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Step 4: Custom Remote Detection (`checkpoint_remote.go`)\\n\\n**Goal**: Before creating/updating `entire-checkpoints`, check if the checkpoint branch already tracks a remote that's neither the default push remote nor `entire-checkpoints`. If so, leave it alone.\\n\\n**New function**:\\n\\n`hasCustomCheckpointRemote(ctx context.Context, pushRemoteName string) bool`:\\n- For each branch (`entire/checkpoints/v1`, `entire/trails/v1`):\\n  - Check `git config branch.<branchName>.remote` (or look at remote tracking refs)\\n  - If the branch has a tracking remote that is neither `pushRemoteName` nor `entire-checkpoints`, return `true`\\n- Actually, the checkpoint branches are pushed with `git push <remote> <branch>` -- they don't necessarily have tracking configured. A better approach: check if remote tracking refs exist for the branch under any remote other than `pushRemoteName` or `entire-checkpoints`. The simplest approach: look for `refs/remotes/*/entire/checkpoints/v1` and check if any match a remote that isn't the push remote or `entire-checkpoints`.\\n- Simpler alternative: just check `git config --get branch.entire/checkpoints/v1.remote`. If it returns a value that's not the push remote or `entire-checkpoints`, respect it.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Step 5: Rewrite `resolvePushSettings` (`checkpoint_remote.go`)\\n\\n**Goal**: Integrate URL derivation, fork detection, and custom remote detection into the push settings resolution.\\n\\n**Rewritten `resolvePushSettings`**:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc resolvePushSettings(ctx context.Context, pushRemoteName string) pushSettings {\\n    s, err := settings.Load(ctx)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return pushSettings{remote: pushRemoteName}\\n    }\\n\\n    ps := pushSettings{\\n        remote:       pushRemoteName,\\n        pushDisabled: s.IsPushSessionsDisabled(),\\n    }\\n\\n    checkpointConfig := s.GetCheckpointRemote()\\n    if checkpointConfig == nil {\\n        return ps\\n    }\\n\\n    // Check if checkpoint branch already tracks a custom remote (not push remote, not entire-checkpoints)\\n    if hasCustomCheckpointRemote(ctx, pushRemoteName) {\\n        logging.Info(ctx, \\\"checkpoint-remote: branch already tracks a custom remote, skipping\\\")\\n        return ps\\n    }\\n\\n    // Get the push remote URL for protocol detection and fork detection\\n    pushRemoteURL, err := getRemoteURL(ctx, pushRemoteName)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        logging.Warn(ctx, \\\"checkpoint-remote: could not get push remote URL\\\",\\n            slog.String(\\\"remote\\\", pushRemoteName),\\n            slog.String(\\\"error\\\", err.Error()),\\n        )\\n        return ps\\n    }\\n\\n    // Fork detection: compare owners\\n    pushOwner := extractOwnerFromRemoteURL(pushRemoteURL)\\n    checkpointOwner := checkpointConfig.Owner()\\n    if pushOwner != \\\"\\\" && checkpointOwner != \\\"\\\" && pushOwner != checkpointOwner {\\n        logging.Warn(ctx, \\\"checkpoint-remote: push remote owner differs from checkpoint remote owner, skipping\\\",\\n            slog.String(\\\"push_owner\\\", pushOwner),\\n            slog.String(\\\"checkpoint_owner\\\", checkpointOwner),\\n        )\\n        return ps\\n    }\\n\\n    // Derive checkpoint URL using same protocol as push remote\\n    checkpointURL, err := deriveCheckpointURL(pushRemoteURL, checkpointConfig.Repo)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        logging.Warn(ctx, \\\"checkpoint-remote: could not derive URL\\\",\\n            slog.String(\\\"error\\\", err.Error()),\\n        )\\n        return ps\\n    }\\n\\n    // Ensure the git remote exists with the derived URL\\n    if err := ensureGitRemote(ctx, checkpointRemoteName, checkpointURL); err != nil {\\n        logging.Warn(ctx, \\\"checkpoint-remote: failed to configure git remote\\\",\\n            slog.String(\\\"error\\\", err.Error()),\\n        )\\n        return ps\\n    }\\n\\n    ps.remote = checkpointRemoteName\\n\\n    // Fetch branches if missing (one-time)\\n    for _, branchName := range []string{paths.MetadataBranchName, paths.TrailsBranchName} {\\n        if err := fetchBranchIfMissing(ctx, checkpointRemoteName, branchName); err != nil {\\n            logging.Warn(ctx, \\\"checkpoint-remote: failed to fetch branch\\\",\\n                slog.String(\\\"branch\\\", branchName),\\n                slog.String(\\\"error\\\", err.Error()),\\n            )\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    return ps\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**New helper**:\\n\\n`getRemoteURL(ctx context.Context, remoteName string) (string, error)`:\\n- Run `git remote get-url <remoteName>` and return the URL\\n- This replaces direct usage of the raw URL from settings\\n\\n**Key change in logging**: Remove `slog.String(\\\"url\\\", ...)` from all log calls to avoid logging URLs that might contain credentials. Instead log `slog.String(\\\"remote\\\", remoteName)` or `slog.String(\\\"repo\\\", checkpointConfig.Repo)`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Step 6: Fix Trails Push Gated by `pushDisabled` (`manual_commit_push.go`)\\n\\n**Goal**: Trails should always push regardless of `push_sessions`. Only checkpoints should be gated.\\n\\n**Change `PrePush`**:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) PrePush(ctx context.Context, remote string) error {\\n    ps := resolvePushSettings(ctx, remote)\\n\\n    // Checkpoints: gated by pushDisabled\\n    if !ps.pushDisabled {\\n        _, pushCheckpointsSpan := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"push_checkpoints_branch\\\")\\n        if err := pushBranchIfNeeded(ctx, ps.remote, paths.MetadataBranchName); err != nil {\\n            pushCheckpointsSpan.RecordError(err)\\n            pushCheckpointsSpan.End()\\n            return err\\n        }\\n        pushCheckpointsSpan.End()\\n    }\\n\\n    // Trails: always push regardless of push_sessions setting\\n    _, pushTrailsSpan := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"push_trails_branch\\\")\\n    err := pushBranchIfNeeded(ctx, ps.remote, paths.TrailsBranchName)\\n    pushTrailsSpan.RecordError(err)\\n    pushTrailsSpan.End()\\n    return err\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe key change is moving the `pushDisabled` check to only gate the checkpoints push, not the trails push. The trails push always happens.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Step 7: Fix Hint Message (`push_common.go`)\\n\\n**Goal**: Mention both settings files in the hint.\\n\\n**Change `printCheckpointRemoteHint`**:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc printCheckpointRemoteHint(remote string) {\\n    if remote != checkpointRemoteName {\\n        return\\n    }\\n    fmt.Fprintln(os.Stderr, \\\"[entire] A checkpoint remote is configured in .entire/settings.json (or .entire/settings.local.json) but could not be reached.\\\")\\n    fmt.Fprintln(os.Stderr, \\\"[entire] Checkpoints are saved locally but not synced. Ensure you have access to the checkpoint remote.\\\")\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Step 8: Fix `fetchBranchIfMissing` Docstring (`checkpoint_remote.go`)\\n\\n**Goal**: The docstring says errors are returned but the implementation swallows them (returns nil on fetch failure).\\n\\n**Fix**: Update the docstring to accurately reflect that fetch failures are swallowed (returned as nil):\\n\\n```go\\n// fetchBranchIfMissing fetches a branch from the remote only if it doesn't exist locally.\\n// This avoids network calls on every push - once the branch exists locally, this is a no-op.\\n// If the fetch fails (remote unreachable, branch doesn't exist on remote), the error is\\n// silently swallowed: the push will handle it. Only fatal errors (opening repo, creating\\n// local branch) are returned.\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Step 9: CLI Flag Parsing (`setup.go`)\\n\\n**Goal**: Change `--checkpoint-remote` from raw URL to `provider:owner/repo` format.\\n\\n**Changes**:\\n\\n1. Update flag description:\\n```go\\ncmd.Flags().StringVar(&opts.CheckpointRemote, \\\"checkpoint-remote\\\", \\\"\\\", \\n    \\\"Checkpoint remote in provider:org/repo format (e.g., github:org/checkpoints-repo)\\\")\\n```\\n\\n2. Update `applyStrategyOptions` to parse the flag and store structured data:\\n```go\\nfunc (opts *EnableOptions) applyStrategyOptions(settings *EntireSettings) {\\n    // ... existing push_sessions logic ...\\n    \\n    if opts.CheckpointRemote != \\\"\\\" {\\n        if settings.StrategyOptions == nil {\\n            settings.StrategyOptions = make(map[string]interface{})\\n        }\\n        // Parse \\\"github:org/repo\\\" format\\n        provider, repo, err := parseCheckpointRemoteFlag(opts.CheckpointRemote)\\n        if err != nil {\\n            // Handle error - could print warning and skip\\n            fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \\\"Warning: invalid --checkpoint-remote format: %v\\\\n\\\", err)\\n            