ile already compiles successfully (confirmed via `go test -run=NOTHING`). The `errors` import is present on line 7. This issue appears to have been resolved already, or the PR review note was incorrect. No changes needed.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Step 13: Update Tests (`checkpoint_remote_test.go`)\\n\\n**Rewrite tests**:\\n\\n1. **Remove** `TestValidateRemoteURL` (no longer validating user-provided URLs) -- or keep if we still validate derived URLs.\\n\\n2. **Add** `TestParseGitRemoteURL` covering:\\n   - SSH SCP format: `git@github.com:org/repo.git`\\n   - HTTPS format: `https://github.com/org/repo.git`\\n   - SSH protocol format: `ssh://git@github.com/org/repo.git`\\n   - With/without `.git` suffix\\n   - Invalid formats\\n\\n3. **Add** `TestDeriveCheckpointURL` covering:\\n   - SSH push remote -> SSH checkpoint URL\\n   - HTTPS push remote -> HTTPS checkpoint URL\\n   - Various host patterns\\n\\n4. **Add** `TestExtractOwnerFromRemoteURL` covering:\\n   - SSH and HTTPS formats\\n   - Returns correct owner\\n\\n5. **Add** `TestCheckForkMismatch` covering:\\n   - Same owner -> no mismatch\\n   - Different owner -> mismatch detected\\n   - Unparseable URL -> no mismatch (conservative)\\n\\n6. **Update** `TestResolvePushSettings_*` tests:\\n   - Change settings JSON from `\\\"checkpoint_remote\\\": \\\"url\\\"` to `\\\"checkpoint_remote\\\": {\\\"provider\\\": \\\"github\\\", \\\"repo\\\": \\\"org/repo\\\"}`\\n   - Add test for fork detection (push remote with different owner)\\n   - Add test for custom remote detection\\n\\n7. **Keep** `TestEnsureGitRemote_*` tests as-is (they test a function that doesn't change).\\n\\n8. **Keep** `TestFetchBranchIfMissing_*` tests as-is.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Implementation Order\\n\\n1. **Step 1**: Settings type change (foundation everything depends on)\\n2. **Step 2**: URL parsing functions (needed by resolvePushSettings)\\n3. **Step 3**: Fork detection (needed by resolvePushSettings)\\n4. **Step 4**: Custom remote detection (needed by reso