to just warn and ignore legacy strings, since this is a brand-new feature that hasn't shipped widely.\\n   - When not set or invalid: return `nil`.\\n\\n3. Add a helper method `Owner()` on `CheckpointRemoteConfig` that extracts the owner from the repo field (split on `/`, take first part).\\n\\n**Changes to `settings/settings_checkpoint_remote_test.go`**:\\n\\nRewrite all tests to reflect the new structured format:\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_NotConfigured` -- returns nil\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_StructuredGithub` -- `{\\\"provider\\\": \\\"github\\\", \\\"repo\\\": \\\"org/checkpoints\\\"}` returns correct config\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_EmptyRepo` -- returns nil\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_LegacyStringIgnored` -- old string format returns nil (or logs warning)\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_WrongType` -- numeric value returns nil\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_JSONRoundTrip` -- load from file, verify structured parsing\\n- `TestGetCheckpointRemote_CoexistsWithPushSessions` -- both settings work together\\n- `TestCheckpointRemoteConfig_Owner` -- verify owner extraction\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Step 2: URL Derivation and Git URL Parsing (new file or in `checkpoint_remote.go`)\\n\\n**Goal**: Add functions to parse a git remote URL and derive a checkpoint URL in the same protocol.\\n\\n**New functions in `checkpoint_remote.go`**:\\n\\n1. `parseGitRemoteURL(remoteURL string) (protocol string, host string, owner string, repo string, err error)`:\\n   - Handle SSH format: `git@github.com:org/repo.git` -> `(\\\"ssh\\\", \\\"github.com\\\", \\\"org\\\", \\\"repo\\\")`\\n   - Handle HTTPS format: `https://github.com/org/repo.git` -> `(\\\"https\\\", \\\"github.com\\\", \\\"org\\\", \\\"repo\\\")`\\n   - Handle SSH with protocol: `ssh://git@github.com/org/repo.git`\\n   - Strip `.git` suffix if present\\n\\n2. `deriveCheckpointURL(pushRemoteURL string, checkpointRepo string) (string, error)`:\\n   - Parse the push remote URL to determine protocol and host\\n   - Construct the