\"soph/add-support-for-different-remote-for-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"refactored-shimmying-meteor\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01Ub78HPse2iQ44YdN7xdXQd\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Here's the updated PR summary:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nAdds support for pushing checkpoint and trails branches to a dedicated remote repository, separate from the user's default push remote. This allows organizations to store session metadata in a different repo (e.g., a private checkpoints repo) while keeping the main repo clean.\\n\\n### Key design decisions\\n\\n- **Structured config format** — `checkpoint_remote` is configured as `{\\\"provider\\\": \\\"github\\\", \\\"repo\\\": \\\"org/repo\\\"}` in `strategy_options`, extensible to future providers\\n- **Protocol auto-detection** — The actual git URL is derived at push time from the push remote's protocol (SSH vs HTTPS), so authentication works automatically without users specifying URLs\\n- **Fork detection** — Compares the push remote's owner to the checkpoint repo owner; skips pushing when they differ (fork scenario where the user likely can't push to the upstream checkpoint repo)\\n- **No named remotes** — Pushes directly to the derived URL (`git push <url> <branch>`) instead of creating/managing a named git remote, avoiding the concern of overwriting user-configured remotes\\n- **Temp refs for URL fetches** — Uses `refs/entire-fetch-tmp/` instead of remote-tracking refs when fetching from URLs, cleaned up after use\\n\\n### Bug fixes\\n\\n- **Trails always push** — `push_sessions: false` now only disables checkpoint pushing; trails are always pushed\\n- **Hint message** — Now mentions both `.entire/settings.json` and `.entire/settings.local.json`\\n\\n### Configuration\\n\\n```json\\n// .entire/settings.json or .entire/settings.local.json\\n{\\n  \\\"strategy_options\\\": {\\n    \\\"checkpoint_remote\\\": {\\n      \\\"provider\\\": \\\"github\\\",\\n      \\\"repo\\\": \\\"org/checkpoints-repo\\\"\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nOr via CLI: `entire enable --checkpoint-remote github:org/checkpoints-repo`\\n\\n### Commits\\n\\n1. **fix: always push trails branch regardless of push_sessions setting**\\n2. **fix: mention both settings files in checkpoint remote hint message**\\n3. **feat: support URL targets in push infrastructure** — `pushBranchIfNeeded`, `doPushBranch`, `fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon` now accept URLs alongside remote names\\n4. **feat: add git URL parsing and protocol detection utilities** — `parseGitRemoteURL`, `deriveCheckpointURL`, `extractOwnerFromRemoteURL`, `redactURL`\\n5. **feat: structured checkpoint_remote config with fork detection** — Settings type change, `resolvePushSettings` rewrite, `fetchBranchIfMissing` URL support, removes old named-remote code\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":286,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":89124,\"output_tokens\":619,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":286,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYwzgrngFVtWHw4wJQcvy\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"747b1f5e-f437-4573-b470-117c58e44ccf\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-11T21:23:01.496Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"747b1f5e-f437-4573-b470-117c58e44ccf\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d79106a5-a980-46f7-b56d-1c2701ed4a9d\",\"version\":\"2.1.72\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/add-support-for-different-remote-for-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"refactored-shimmying-meteor\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentT