hals.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. **Unnecessary `AbsPath()` Calls with Fallback Pattern**\\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go` lines 90-99 and setup.go\\n\\n**Issue:** \\n```go\\nsettingsFileAbs, err := paths.AbsPath(ctx, EntireSettingsFile)\\nif err != nil {\\n    settingsFileAbs = EntireSettingsFile  // Fallback to relative\\n}\\nlocalSettingsFileAbs, err := paths.AbsPath(ctx, EntireSettingsLocalFile)\\nif err != nil {\\n    localSettingsFileAbs = EntireSettingsLocalFile  // Fallback to relative\\n}\\n```\\n\\nEach `AbsPath()` calls `WorktreeRoot()`, which runs `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` (a subprocess). When errors occur (e.g., outside repo), this subprocess runs unnecessarily only to be discarded.\\n\\n**Impact:** Subprocess overhead in error paths. The fallback pattern makes the subprocess call redundant when not in a git repo.\\n\\n**Recommendation:** Check git repo status first before calling `AbsPath()`, or accept relative paths directly for settings loading.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. **Repeated File Existence Checks (TOCTOU Anti-pattern)**\\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go` lines 269-276 and setup.go\\n\\n**Issue:** \\n```go\\nfunc IsSetUp(ctx context.Context) bool {\\n    settingsFileAbs, err := paths.AbsPath(ctx, EntireSettingsFile)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return false\\n    }\\n    _, err = os.Stat(settingsFileAbs)\\n    return err == nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThen `IsSetUpAndEnabled()` (lines 281-290) calls `IsSetUp()` AND `Load()`:\\n- `IsSetUp()` does `os.Stat()` \\n- `Load()` does `os.ReadFile()`\\n\\nTwo filesystem operations for the same file in rapid succession.\\n\\nSimilarly in setup.go line 123, `IsEmptyRepository()` is called; then if needed, `OpenRepository()` is called again.\\n\\n**Impact:** Unnecessary filesystem round-trips; potential TOCTOU race (file could change between check and use, though generally benign here).\\n\\n**Recommendation:** Combine into single operation: `os.ReadFile()` already returns an error if file doesn't exist.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. **Hot-Path Settings Loading in `PrePush` Hook**\\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/checkpoint_remote.go` lines 63-126\\n\\n**Issue:** `resolvePushSettings()` calls `settings.Load()` which:\\n1. Reads `.entire/settings.json` from disk\\n2. Parses JSON\\n3. Then attempts to read and merge `.entire/settings.local.json` (even if not needed)\\n4. For each checkpoint URL, runs `git remote get-url` (subprocess)\\n5. Parses the URL\\n6. Calls `fetchBranchIfMissing()` twice (lines 116-123), which:\\n   - Opens the git repository\\n   - Checks if branches exist\\n   - Runs `git fetch` (with 30-second timeout)\\n\\n**Impact:** Pre-push hook runs on every `git push`. The subprocess calls and fetch operations are expensive. The fetch is only a \\\"one-time\\\" optimization, but if the branch doesn't exist locally AND doesn't exist remotely, this is 30 seconds of timeout per push.\\n\\n**Recommendation:** \\n- Cache settings per process lifetime (or shorter TTL)\\n- Move branch fetch to only when push fails, not speculatively\\n- Consider skipping fetch entirely if remote is unreachable (the comment says push handles it gracefully)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. **Inefficient Settings Merging Logic**\\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go` lines 159-264\\n\\n**Issue:** The mergeJSON function handles 11 separate fields with individual validation. Each field follows the same pattern:\\n- Check if key exists (hash map lookup)\\n- Unmarshal that field\\n- Validate\\n\\nFor `strategy_options` (a map), it merges by iterating: \\\"if settings.StrategyOptions is nil, assign, else iterate and merge\\\" (lines 220-227). But `strategy_options` can be modified multiple times if loading from multiple sources.\\n\\n**Impact:** Unnecessary allocations and iterations; quadratic behavior if settings are loaded and merged repeatedly in a session.\\n\\n**Recommendation:** Use a helper function to unmarshal and validate a single field, or redesign to unmarshal the entire struct once and only override explicitly-set fields.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. **Subprocess in Critical Loop (Fork Detection)**\\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/checkpoint_remote.go` lines 79-87\\n\\n**Issue:**\\n```go\\npushRemoteURL, err := getRemoteURL(ctx, pushRemoteName)  // Runs git remote get-url\\n```\\n\\nThis subprocess runs every time `resolvePushSettings()` is called, even if checkpoint_remote is not configured. It's not conditional on the config existing.\\n\\n**Impact:** Unnecessary subprocess overhead when checkpoint_remote is not configured (the common case).\\n\\n**Recommendation:** Move `getRemoteURL()` call inside the `if config != nil` block.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 7. **Unused Repository Handle in `fetchBranchIfMissing`**\\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/checkpoint_remote.go` lines 263-312\\n\\n**Issue:** \\n- Opens repository (line 264)\\n- Checks if branch exists locally (line 271)\\n- **Returns early** (line 272) if it exists\\n- Only **after** return does it attempt fetch\\n\\nBut if fetch happens:\\n- Repository is opened **again** inside `fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon()` (line 154 in push_common.go)\\n\\n**Impact:** Repository opened twice when fetch is needed; once unnecessarily if branch exists locally.\\n\\n**Recommendation:** In `fetchBranchIfMissing()`, keep the repo handle and reuse it for the fetch operation if needed.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Summary of Severity:\\n\\n| Issue | Severity | Impact |\\n|-------|----------|--------|\\n| Redundant JSON parsing in mergeJSON | **HIGH** | 10-12 unmarshals per Load() call |\\n| Settings loading in PrePush hook | **HIGH** | Runs on every git push; includes expensive fetches |\\n| Fork detection getRemoteURL unconditional | **MEDIUM** | Subprocess runs even when feature not configured |\\n| Merged file existence checks | **LOW-MEDIUM** | Extra filesystem ops; minor regression only |\\n| Redundant AbsPath calls with errors | **LOW** | Only impacts error paths |\\n| Repository handle duplication | **LOW** | Affects only checkpoint fetch path |\\n\\n**Most critical fix:** Simplify `mergeJSON()` to avoid N+1 parsing, and move `getRemoteURL()` inside the config check in `resolvePushSettings()`.</result>\\n<usage><total_tokens>66587</total_tokens><tool_uses>14</tool_uses><duration_ms>36411</duration_ms></usage>\\n</task-notification>\\nFull transcript available at: /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-soph-Work-entire-devenv-cli/tasks/a488557b64fe27a24.output\"},\"uuid\":\"62ea0d7c-3523-4466-9c7c-cde5ffa3eb5d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-11T22:19:10.380Z\",\"permissionMode\":\"acceptEdits\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"62ea0d7c-3523-4466-9c7c-cde5ffa3eb5d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d79106a5-a980-46f7-b56d-1c2701ed4a9d\",\"version\":\"2.1.72\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/add-support-for-different-remote-for-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"refactored-shimmying-meteor\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01L12dhHDJDVt3T1M5Wmv6yK\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\nThe background agents completed with a few additional findings. Let me check the one actionable new finding — the `getRemoteURL()` call happening unconditionally before the `config != nil` check:\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4372,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":109288,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":4372},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYx4zMiuwoH2Q9W9p4DLq\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"6eec0edc-9a55-4ec4-8d9a-c81232ad653a\",\"tim