Low value—mostly I/O. |\\n| `tryPushSessionsCommon()` | ❌ No | **Gap**: Executes `git push --no-verify`. Edge cases: (1) success, (2) non-fast-forward error (special case), (3) other error. Requires context timeout and error classification (the \\\"non-fast-forward\\\" string matching). Worth testing to ensure error messages are correctly identified. |\\n| `fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon()` | ❌ No | **Critical Gap**: Complex merge logic. Tests needed for: (1) fetch succeeds, trees merged, merge commit created, ref updated; (2) URL target uses temp ref, remote name uses standard remote-tracking ref; (3) reconciliation of disconnected metadata branch; (4) tree flattening and entry merging; (5) cleanup of temp ref. This is a major code path (~100 lines) with multiple integration points. |\\n| `isURL()` | ✅ Yes | `TestIsURL` covers all cases (remote name, SSH SCP, HTTPS, SSH protocol). Good. |\\n| `PushTrailsBranch()` | ❌ No | **Gap**: Public function. It's a wrapper around `pushBranchIfNeeded()`, but without tests for the wrapper, there's no integration-level coverage. Should test that it pushes the trails branch specifically. |\\n| `createMergeCommitCommon()` | ❌ No | **Gap**: Creates a commit object with multiple parents, encodes it, stores it. Untested: (1) success path, (2) encoding failure, (3) storage failure. Medium complexity. |\\n\\n**Verdict**: `push_common.go` has **0 tests** for critical push/merge logic. The two most important missing tests are `TestDoPushBranch` (recovery flow) and `TestFetchAndMergeSessionsCommon` (tree merging).\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### **MANUAL_COMMIT_PUSH.GO** (`manual_commit_push.go` - 1 function)\\n\\n| Function | Tested | Assessment |\\n|----------|--------|-----------|\\n| `PrePush()` | ❌ No | **Critical Gap**: Public hook entry point. Orchestrates: (1) load settings once, (2) resolve push settings (including fork detection), (3) conditional checkpoint push (respects `push_sessions` disable), (4) unconditional trails push. No test verifies that: (a) checkpoint push is skipped when `push_sessions: false`, (b) checkpoint URL is used when configured, (c) trails always push to user's remote, (d) settings load errors are handled. This is the top-level contract—worth at least one integration test. |\\n\\n**Verdict**: **No tests** for the entry point.\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### **CHECKPOINT_REMOTE.GO** (`checkpoint_remote.go` - 11 functions)\\n\\n| Function | Tested | Assessment |\\n|----------|--------|-----------|\\n| `resolvePushSettings()` | ✅ Partial | `TestResolvePushSettings_*` covers: NoConfig, PushDisabled, HTTPS/SSH derivation, ForkDetection, LegacyStringIgnored. **Gap**: No test for the branch fetch-on-miss behavior (lines 125-132). This is important: fetches `entire/checkpoints/v1` and `entire/trails/v1` if they don't exist locally, but silently succeeds if remote is unreachable. Test needed to verify: (1) branches are fetched if missing, (2) fetch failures are silent (logging but no error). |\\n| `parseGitRemoteURL()` | ✅ Yes | `TestParseGitRemoteURL` covers SSH SCP, SSH protocol, HTTPS, with/without .git. Comprehensive. |\\n| `splitOwnerRepo()` | ❌ No | **Gap**: Small helper, but tested **indirectly** via `parseGitRemoteURL` test cases (which call it internally). Direct test could add edge cases: (1) empty parts, (2) leading/trailing slashes. Minor—low priority. |\\n| `deriveCheckpointURL()` | ✅ Yes | `TestDeriveCheckpointURL` covers SSH and HTTPS derivation with various hosts. Good. |\\n| `deriveCheckpointURLFromInfo()` | ❌ No | **Gap**: Tested **indirectly** via `deriveCheckpointURL` and `resolvePushSettings`. Direct test unnecessary unless edge case added. |\\n| `extractOwnerFromRemoteURL()` | ✅ Yes | `TestExtractOwnerFromRemoteURL` covers SSH, HTTPS, and error case (returns empty string). Good. |\\n| `getRemoteURL()` | ❌ No | **Gap**: Shells out to `git remote get-url`. Untested: (1) success, (2) remote not found (error case). Low value—minimal logic, just a shell wrapper. Could test in integratio